{{BLP sources|date=July 2015}} {{Infobox criminal | name = Bjarte Baasland | image_name = | image_size = | image_caption = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1974|03|05}} | birth_place = [[Norway]] | death_date = | death_place = | charge = [[Fraud]] | conviction_penalty = Sentenced to four years in prison | conviction_status = | occupation = Former businessman | spouse = | parents = | children = }}
'''Bjarte Baasland''' (born 5 March 1974) is a former Norwegian businessman and convicted [[fraudster]].
He became famous in Norway in connection with the ''Baasland case'' in the autumn of 2008, when it was revealed that he had [[Problem gambling|gambled]] away almost {{NOK|60 million}} (more than €7 million) that he borrowed from family friends and banks.<ref name="Norway 2008a">{{cite web |last=Norway |first=Aftenposten |title=Baasland lost a fortune gambling - Aftenposten.no |website=aftenposten.no |date=2008-10-20 |url=http://www.aftenposten.no/english/local/article2659341.ece |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081020090928/http://www.aftenposten.no/english/local/article2659341.ece |archive-date=2008-10-20 |dead-url=yes |access-date=2018-06-19}}</ref> He is the son of [[Ernst Baasland]], who at the time was a [[Diocese of Stavanger|Bishop of Stavanger]] in the [[Church of Norway]]. A consequence of the Baasland case was that Ernst Baasland resigned as Bishop<ref name="www.newsinenglish.no 2017">{{cite web |title=No apologies as bishop bows out |website=www.newsinenglish.no |date=2009-06-08 |url=http://www.newsinenglish.no/2009/06/08/no-apologies-as-bishop-bows-out/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170703085016/http://www.newsinenglish.no/2009/06/08/no-apologies-as-bishop-bows-out/ |archive-date=2017-07-03 |dead-url=no |access-date=2018-06-19}}</ref> and went personally bankrupt<ref name="Norway 2008b">{{cite web |last=Norway |first=Aftenposten |title=Bankruptcy claim filed against bishop - Aftenposten.no |website=aftenposten.no |date=2008-09-12 |url=http://www.aftenposten.no/english/local/article2605472.ece |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080912004810/http://www.aftenposten.no/english/local/article2605472.ece |archive-date=2008-09-12 |dead-url=yes |access-date=2018-06-19}}</ref> along with his wife, Bodhild Baasland, who is also under investigation for fraud. On 2 October 2009, Bjarte Baasland was convicted of fraud and sentenced to 4 years in prison and to return NOK 26,6 million to one of his creditors, [[Cecilie Nustad]].<ref name=Aftenposten>{{cite web|last=Holm |first=Annar |title=Baasland dømt til fire års fengsel |url=http://www.aftenposten.no/nyheter/iriks/article3300448.ece#.UciGITQ2aIU |publisher=Aftenposten |accessdate=24 June 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121003060505/http://www.aftenposten.no/nyheter/iriks/article3300448.ece |archivedate=3 October 2012 |df= }}</ref> Baasland fooled mainly his mother to lend him money for business projects. She borrowed money from banks, her husband, and her close friend Cecilie Nustad.
